[0m[49m[39m  147, 149[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  148, 150[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  149, 151[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  150, 152[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[39m  151, 153[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Comprehend Medical, Amazon SageMaker, Amazon S3, AWS Lambda, Amazon DynamoDB |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 152     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint` (scoped to `arn:aws:sagemaker:{region}:{account}:endpoint/assertion-classifier-*`), `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query` |
[0m[49m[39m  153, 155[0m:[39m[49m | **BAA** | AWS BAA signed (clinical notes are PHI) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 154     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; SageMaker endpoint: inter-container encryption enabled; all API calls over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 155     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Lambda and SageMaker in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, Comprehend Medical, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; SageMaker endpoint: turn on inter-container encryption (prevents data leaking between inference containers on shared hardware); all API calls over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Lambda and SageMaker in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, Comprehend Medical, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs. SageMaker endpoint: deploy with VPC configuration (PrivateLink) so inference traffic stays within the private network. Deploy across at least 2 AZs for production resilience. |
[0m[49m[39m  156, 158[0m:[39m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled: log all Comprehend Medical and SageMaker API calls for audit |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 157     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Sample Data** | i2b2 2010 assertion corpus (requires DUA), MIMIC-III notes (requires PhysioNet credentials), or internally annotated clinical notes. Never use real PHI in dev without appropriate safeguards. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Data Lifecycle** | DynamoDB TTL configured per institutional records retention policy (typically 7-10 years for adult records, longer for minors). S3 lifecycle policy for archived notes. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Sample Data** | i2b2 2010 assertion corpus (requires a Data Use Agreement, which takes 2-4 weeks to get approved), MIMIC-III notes (requires PhysioNet credentials), or internally annotated clinical notes. Never use real PHI in dev without appropriate safeguards. |
[0m[49m[39m  158, 161[0m:[39m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Comprehend Medical: ~$0.01 per 100 characters. SageMaker real-time endpoint (ml.m5.xlarge): ~$0.23/hour. At 50 notes/hour, roughly $0.005/note for inference. Total: ~$0.02/note. |
[0m[49m[39m  159, 162[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  160, 163[0m:[39m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[39m  161, 164[0m:[39m[49m 
